A '''Danophone''' is a person that speaks the [[Danish language]] either natively or by adoption. As an adjective it means "Danish-speaking." Most Danophones reside in [[Denmark]] as well as [[Greenland]] and the [[Faroe Islands]], both Danish territories. There is also a small Danophone population living in the region of [[Schleswig-Holstein]] in northern [[Germany]], along the border with Denmark.

